data.chText: 无用的东西；无价值的东西
data.enText: things that are considered useless or of little value

data.chText: 我把阁楼里所有的废旧杂物都清除干净了。
data.enText: I've cleared out all that old junk in the attic.

data.chText: 这件瓷器是从旧货店里买来的。
data.enText: This china came from a junk shop .

data.chText: 电视上全是些无聊的东西。
data.enText: There's nothing but junk on the TV.

data.chText: 中国式帆船
data.enText: a Chinese boat with a square sail and a flat bottom

data.chText: 把…当作废物扔弃；丢弃；废弃
data.enText: to get rid of sth because it is no longer valuable or useful

data.text: things ♦ stuff ♦ possessions ♦ junk ♦ belongings ♦ goods ♦ valuables

data.chText: 以上各词均指东西、物品，尤指个人拥有或随身携带的物件。
data.enText: These are all words for objects or items, especially ones that you own or have with you at a particular time.
things

data.chText: 指个人拥有或作特定用途的物品、衣服、用具：
data.enText: ( rather informal ) objects, clothing or tools that you own or that are used for a particular purpose

data.chText: 我帮你打点行装好吗？
data.enText: Shall I help you pack your things?

data.chText: 随身带上游泳用品。
data.enText: Bring your swimming things.
stuff

data.chText: 指名称不详、名称无关紧要或所指明确的东西、物品、玩意儿：
data.enText: [U] ( informal ) used to refer to a group of objects when you do not know their names, when the names are not important or when it is obvious what you are talking about

data.chText: 我那些东西都哪儿去了？
data.enText: Where's all my stuff?
possessions

data.chText: 指个人财产、私人物品，尤指动产：
data.enText: things that you own, especially sth that can be moved

data.chText: 囚犯除信件和照片外不允许有任何私人物品。
data.enText: Prisoners were allowed no personal possessions except letters and photographs.
junk

data.chText: 指无用的东西、无价值的东西：
data.enText: [U] things that are considered useless or of little value

data.chText: 我把阁楼里所有的废旧杂物都清除干净了。
data.enText: I've cleared out all that old junk from the attic.
belongings

data.chText: 指动产，尤指随身物品：
data.enText: possessions that can be moved, especially ones that you have with you at a particular time

data.chText: 请确保在下飞机前带好所有的随身物品。
data.enText: Please make sure you have all your belongings with you when leaving the plane.
goods

data.chText: 指动产、（可搬运的）私人财产：
data.enText: ( rather formal or technical ) possessions that can be moved

data.chText: 他被判犯销赃罪。
data.enText: He was found guilty of handling stolen goods .
valuables

data.chText: 尤指私人的贵重物品（如首饰、相机等）：
data.enText: things that are worth a lot of money, especially small personal things such as jewellery or cameras

data.chText: 现金或其他贵重物品请勿乱放。
data.enText: Never leave cash or other valuables lying around.
personal things/stuff/possessions/belongings
worldly possessions/belongings/goods
to collect/gather/pack (up) your/the things/stuff/possessions/belongings
to go through/look through/search sb's/your/the things/stuff/possessions/belongings

ex.enText: Tom went to dump the garbage.

ex.chText: 垃圾污染我们的河川湖泊。
ex.enText: Garbage pollutes our rivers and lakes.

synonyms.bx: 多指生活中的有机废料，如废纸、包装盒、剩饭剩菜或变质的食物等。

ex.chText: 沟渠中塞满了淤泥和垃圾。
ex.enText: The ditches had filled up with mud and debris.

ex.chText: 你在现场时，碎渣等垃圾是否清除掉了？
ex.enText: Was the debris removed in your presence?

synonyms.bx: 指某处堆积的垃圾或某种材料无用的碎渣、碎片等。

ex.enText: There is a heap of junk in the corner.

ex.chText: 他把汽车行李箱中所有废旧杂物都扔掉了。
ex.enText: He threw away all the junk in the boot of his car.

synonyms.bx: 指没有用处、毫无价值的废旧物品。

ex.enText: There were piles of litter in the streets.

synonyms.bx: 尤指在公共场所散落于地、有碍观瞻的废弃物。

ex.chText: 他们将花园中的垃圾全部烧掉了。
ex.enText: They burnt up all the garden rubbish.

ex.chText: 垃圾工每周来收一次垃圾。
ex.enText: The dustman comes once a week to collect the rubbish.

ex.chText: 天哪，他桌上有那么多垃圾！
ex.enText: Oh God, he's got so much rubbish on his desk!

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指扔掉的食物、废纸等；也可指任何不再使用而应该扔掉的东西，但作此义解时多用于非正式文体。

ex.chText: 把所有垃圾放进这只袋子里。
ex.enText: Put all the waste in this bag.

ex.chText: 他们把城里的垃圾倒入海中。
ex.enText: They disposed of the city's waste in the sea.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，多指已无使用价值的材料或陈旧的、破损的物品，也可指任何被丢弃之物。

tr: any of various Chinese boats with a high poop and lugsails
the remains of something that has been destroyed or broken up

value.def: Junk is old and used goods that have little value and that you do not want any more.

example.ex: Rose finds her furniture in junk shops...
example.tran: 罗丝从旧货店买来了家具。

example.ex: What are you going to do with all that junk, Larry?
example.tran: 这一大堆破烂儿你打算怎么处理，拉里？

value.def: If you junk something, you get rid of it or stop using it.

example.ex: Consumers will not have to junk their old cassettes to use the new format...
example.tran: 消费者将不必丢弃他们的旧盒带而采用新的制式。

example.ex: The Socialists junked dogma when they came to office in 1982.
example.tran: 社会党人1982年上台执政后，就把其政治信条弃之不顾。

value.def: A junk is a Chinese sailing boat that has a flat bottom and square sails.
